.TH FLNAV 1 "May 2026" "flnav 1.0.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
flnav \- forensic log navigator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B flnav
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B flnav
is a fork of lnav, the Logfile Navigator, with added features for log
analysis, security investigation, and forensic triage.
.PP
It can be installed alongside upstream
.B lnav
because it uses a separate binary name, configuration directory, and database
schema.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --ioc " FILE"
Load a plain-text IOC file and highlight matching IPv4 addresses in the log
view and forensic reports.
.TP
.B -c
Execute a command after loading files.
.TP
.B -n
Run in headless mode.
.SH FORENSIC COMMANDS
.TP
.B :normalize-timestamps [on|off]
Toggle UTC timestamp normalization in the log view.
.TP
.B :ssh-stats
Show the SSH Traffic Flow Map.
.TP
.B :session-trace ACTOR [...]
Trace one or more IP addresses or usernames across loaded logs.
.TP
.B :log-gaps [THRESHOLD]
Report gaps in log activity. Thresholds accept seconds, minutes, or hours
using suffixes like 30s, 10m, or 2h.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.flnav
Default user configuration directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
Upstream lnav documentation is available at
.UR https://docs.lnav.org
.UE .
.PP
The flnav project page is
.UR https://github.com/jeffreydgz/flnav
.UE .
